        <section id="uses-comp">
            <h>complement</h>
            <p>Like other (proper) nouns, <g>Calum</g> can be used as the complement of a <a
                    href="?xx=prepositions/prepositions">preposition</a>.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Cha robh falt dubh <m>air Calum</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>Calum did not have black hair.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an cù còmhla <m>ri Calum</m> anns an achadh an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>The dog is with Malcolm in the field today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
